@food1
view-if: food1_visited = 0
on-arrival: food1_visited = 1
on-display: {!  
    var cardEl = document.createElement('div');  
    cardEl.className = "face-figure2";  

    var image = new Image();  
    image.className = "face-img";  
    image.src = "img/IMG_0113.jpeg";  

    cardEl.appendChild(image);  
    var contentDiv = document.querySelector("#page #mid_panel #content");
    contentDiv.appendChild(cardEl);
!}

<p>Lamb Stew is a traditional Anglophone dish, but was actually invented in Ireland as a peasant dish. It generally consists of <span stlye="color:#F9CBD3;">lamb</span>, <span style="color:#E16E6E;">beef</span>, or <span style="color;#F1EEDB;">chicken</span> stock, lamb, and varied <span style="color:#008000;">vegetables</span>, like <span style="color:#ff0000;">carrots</span>, <span style="color:#895129;">potatoes</span>, <span style="color:8eab12;">peas</span>, and <span style="color:#A29A91;">mushrooms</span></p><br /><br />
<p>One of the influences I have when eating this dish is a cultural influence - I was born in northern <span style="color:#ffffff;">England</span> (<span style="color:#CF142B;">New</span><span style="color:#F7E017;">cas</span><span style="color:#CF142B;">tle</span> upon <span style="color:#344B9E;">T</span><span style="color:#FFFFFF;">yn</span><span style="color:#344B9E;">e</span>) where stews are a very common dish, especially in the cool season (e.g. not mid-to-late summer). I was also raised in <span style="color:#C8102E;">Denmark</span>, where stews are also pretty common</p><br /><br />
<p>The other influence I have  when eating this dish is a family influence - Every <span stlye="color:#80EF80;">Easter</span>, as well as on other special occasions, my family has <span stlye="color:#F9CBD3;">lamb</span> for dinner.</p><br /><br />

- @goto_menu

