    contentDiv.appendChild(cardEl);
!}

<p>Licorice (Specifically Liquorice Allsorts) was a type of candy invented in 1899, in Leicester, Britain. It is a sweet that has many mixed opinions - Many people like it, especially europeans, and many don't like it.</p><br /><br />
<pThe first influence for this food is an emotional one - I really like licorice, and I will often eat it when I am stressed, assuming I have any.</p><br /><br />
<p>The second influence for this food is an availabiltiy one - I can easily pick up licorice, by going to Walmart, BulkBarn, Dollarama, or Longo's. Additionally, a small bag if licorice isn't all that expensive - At Dollarama, you can get a bag for $2.25 after tax.</p><br /><br />

- @goto_menu

