<p>A Hotdog is a large piece of processed meat wrapped inside an intestine, usually of pig. They are cheap and plentiful, though lack in flavour</p><br /><br />
<p>The first influence for this food is a social one - Often, when I go to parties or similar to social occasions, one of the food choices is hotdogs, especially at Barbecue's. Because there is oftne little other choice, I will eat a hotdog</p><br /><br />
<p>The second influence for this food is a media one - Hotdogs are ubiquitous in North American culture - You see them everywhere, in advertisements, social media posts, storybooks, TV shows, even tattoos. As they are hard to escape seeing, they infest your mind wuith thoughts of hotdogs.</p><br /><br />

- @goto_menu

